description: TEHRAN – Iran defeated Kyrgyzstan 3-0 Friday night and won 2024 CAFA U20 Championship.
title: Iran crowned champions of 2024 CAFA U20

description: TEHRAN- Iran's Minister of Interior announced the conclusion of agreement between Iran and Iraq to construct a shipping line from Khorramshahr to Basra to strengthen commercial transportation between the two countries.
title: Iran, Iraq collaborate on new Khorramshahr-Basra shipping route: official

description: TEHRAN – Amir Saeed Iravani, Iran's Ambassador and Permanent Representative to the United Nations, has strongly refuted claims made by the U.S. representative during a Security Council meeting regarding the situation in Yemen.
title: Iran rebuts U.S. allegations at UN Security Council over Yemen conflict

description: TEHRAN – On Thursday, Iran’s President-elect Masoud Pezeshkian visited the home of the late Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi, whom he will be succeeding after winning runoff presidential elections on July 5.
title: Pezeshkian honors legacy of late Raisi with family visit

description: TEHRAN - In an analysis, Donya-e-Eqtesad discussed the challenges of the recent agreement between India and Iran and wrote: For India, Chabahar can be an opportunity to evade the economic pressures of the United States, while for Iran, any foreign investment to counter the sanctions is welcomed.
title: Prospects for Chabahar project

description: TEHRAN – The Bushehr Province Police Command, through its public relations office, has announced the arrest of a group responsible for a series of vandalism and arson incidents across the province.
title: Police report arrest of terrorist group in Southern Iranian province

description: TEHRAN – Iran's President-elect, Masoud Pezeshkian, has appointed former Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif as the head of the Strategic Council on Foreign Relations for the transition period in his first presidential decree.
title: Zarif to lead transitional council responsible for evaluating government candidates

description: TEHRAN – Russia’s willingness to promote mutual cooperation with Iran is unwavering, declared Russian President Vladimir Putin during a meeting with Iran’s Parliament Speaker Mohammad Baqer Qalibaf on the sidelines of the 10th BRICS Parliamentary Forum.
title: Iran-Russia cooperation will continue to grow: Putin

description: TEHRAN – A senior Iranian military official has emphasized Iran's unwavering commitment to supporting regional Resistance movements in their struggle against Israel.
title: Iranian commander reaffirms ‘strategic support’ for Resistance groups

description: TEHRAN – In a letter to the Head of Hamas’ political bureau Ismail Haniyeh, Iran’s President-elect Masoud Pezeshkian thanked the Palestinian leader for his earlier felicitations, declaring that his country will continue to back Palestine until its liberation from Zionist occupiers.
title: Iran’s support for Palestine to continue until ‘liberation of Al-Quds’: Pezeshkian

description: TEHRAN – On May 19, 2024, the untimely passing of President Ebrahim Raisi- a deeply respected and dedicated public servant- in a tragic helicopter crash precipitated early elections in Iran, marking a pivotal moment in our nation's history.
title: My message to the new world

description:
* A collection of paintings by Shirin Moayya is currently on view in an exhibition at Baa Gallery. 
The exhibit entitled “Illusion” will run until July 26 at the gallery located at No. 1, Nastaran Alley, Nakhl St., Artesh Boulevard.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN-The 72nd Melbourne International Film Festival (MIFF), to be held from August 8 to 25 in Australia, has dedicated a special section to the Iranian classic films.
title: Iranian New Wave cinema to be reviewed at 72nd Melbourne International Film Festival

description: VITEBSK, Belarus- The Slavic Bazaar held its 33rd festival in the Belarusian city of Vitebsk on Thursday evening.
title: Belarus holds 33rd Slavic Bazaar Festival to promote peace

description: TEHRAN- The results of the Israeli army’s first investigation into failures during the surprise military operation by the Palestinian Hamas resistance movement on October 7 have led to widespread criticism and embarrassment for the regime.

In recent weeks, the Zionist colonial regime released 55 Palestinian prisoners who were detained in Gaza during the genocidal operation initiated by Israel months ago.

description: Lebanon’s Hezbollah resistance movement said it has targeted the Israeli military forces and equipment.

title: US to resume shipments of 500lb bombs to Israel

description: Pakistan's Supreme Court ruled on Friday that jailed former Prime Minister Imran Khan's party was eligible for over 20 extra reserved seats in parliament, ramping up pressure on the country's weak coalition government, Reuters reported.
title: Imran Khan's party wins reserved seats in Pakistan's parliament

description: Canadian police have clashed with pro-Palestinian protesters in Montreal.

description: TEHRAN – On Thursday, Muhammad Shahryar, the consul-general of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan in Mashhad, along with his accompanying delegation, visited the Nader Shah mausoleum in the northeastern Iranian metropolis.

description: TEHRAN - In a bid to invigorate summer tourism, the Kish Free Zone Organization is partnering with private tour operators to significantly increase the number of flights to the island, according to a local official.

description: TEHRAN- As announced by the director general of the Iranian Ministry of Agriculture’s Office of Quality Improvement, Processing, and Aquatic Market, the value of Iran’s fishery export increased by over 30 percent during the first quarter of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-June 20), as compared to the same period of time in the past year.

description: TEHRAN - The leaders in the men’s and women’s National teams ranking have remained the same in the most recent update as Brazil and Spain remain in pole positions.
title: Iran unchanged at world beach soccer ranking

description: TEHRAN – A sum of one trillion rials (around $1.7 million) has been allocated to supporting one percent most-cited researchers nationally and globally in the current Iranian year that started on March 19.

description: The Archipelago 2024 project-educational intensive has started its work in Russia. The event takes place from 8 to 21 July on Sakhalin. One of its key goals is to present unifying meanings, super tasks and results in a number of areas of scientific and technological development of the country. TV BRICS is the international media partner of the event.
title: Archipelago 2024 to present new markets, industries and initiatives of Russia

description: TEHRAN –The General Assembly has adopted a draft resolution called ‘United Nations Decade (2025-2034) on Combating Sand and Dust Storms (SDSs)’, the 11th resolution on addressing SDSs since 2016.

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Oil Minister Javad Oji says the country’s oil production has increased from 2.2 million barrels per day (bpd) in 2021, when the current government took office, to 3.6 million bpd in the current year, IRIB reported.

description: In December 1978, China initiated reforms to transition from a planned economy to a market economy, continuously advancing market-oriented reforms since then, with the role of market mechanisms in resource allocation steadily strengthening. With the deepening of the reform and opening-up, China's economy has grown exponentially, with market entities such as domestic enterprises, individual businesses and foreign-invested institutions emerging rapidly.
title: China's market-oriented reforms: Always ongoing and never completed

description: TEHRAN - One of the winningest Iran’s volleyball players of the last decade, Farhad Ghaemi announced the end of his playing career.
title: Iranian volleyball spiker Ghaemi ends playing career
